==English==

===Etymology===
Old English [[tima|tīma]].

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:AHD|AHD]]: tīm
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /taɪm/
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /<tt>taIm</tt>/

====Homophones====
*[[thyme]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

#The inevitable passing of events from future to present then past.
#:''You had plenty of time to finish your homework, but you waited until the last minute.''
#The moment indicated by a clock or other time-measuring device.
#:''What time is it?'', ''The time is ten o'clock''.
#A particular occasion.
#: ''See you another time''
#: ''Last time I was here''.

